17/08/2006
BELGRADE, Serbia -- President Boris Tadic has offered his Kosovo counterpart, Fatmir Sejdiu, medical aid to help fight a meningitis epidemic in the province. 
According to a statement from Tadic's office on Wednesday (16 August), he proposed -- via UNMIK -- that Belgrade send medicines, equipment and epidemiological assistance. 
Some 267 patients have been admitted to a Pristina hospital with meningitis, most from northeast municipalities. 
(Danas - 17/08/06; Tanjug - 16/08/06)
